cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of information-theoretic measures to analyse the dynamics of complex systems, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category as it directly relates to the topic of the paper. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely as the paper mentions the domains of computational neuroscience and Artificial Life. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the dynamics of operations in space and time, which could be relevant to these sub-categories.
